Agility, Industries Qatar and Sabic: Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-06-07T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/agility-industries-qatar-and-sabic-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close.  Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  retreated 0.2 percent, while Abu
Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  advanced 0.5 percent. Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM) 
declined 0.5 percent.        Agility (AGLTY)  : The Kuwaiti company will focus on
commercial logistics and emerging-market expansion to boost
income as it fights a legal battle in the U.S. and following a
27 percent plunge in its share price this year, Managing
Director Tarek Sultan said in an interview. The shares were
unchanged at 380 fils.        Saudi Basic Industries Corp. (SABIC)  : Crude for July
delivery dropped as much as 1.4 percent to $98.80 a barrel in
electronic trading on the New York Mercantile Exchange
yesterday. Saudi Basic, or Sabic, is the world’s largest
petrochemicals maker. The shares were unchanged at 104.75
riyals. Industries Qatar (IQCD QD), the  Middle East ’s second-
biggest petrochemicals company, decreased 2.7 percent to 131.9
riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
